The Waterloo School District is offering enrolled students "grab and go" meals this school year. The first week of meals (all meals at once) will be available for PICK-UP on Wednesday, August 19th from 4 pm to 6 pm at the Waterloo High School Cafeteria.

If you are requesting for more than one student in your household, please complete a separate form for each child you are requesting meals for.

Meals will be charged to your student's lunch account per their free, reduced or paid meal status. (We encourage any family in need of meal assistance to apply for this program.)

post_text:
The Waterloo School District will be offering students "grab and go" meals this school year beginning on August 19th, 2020. Meals will be available for PICK-UP EACH DAY at one of our schools. This survey is only to assist us in determining the interest of our student body at this time.

Meals will be charged to your student's lunch account per their free, reduced or paid meal status. The free and reduced application is available in your email or on our website. We encourage all eligible families to apply. Applications should be returned to the Cafeteria Director, Ruth Mason.

If you are interested in meals for your child(ren), please complete one survey per registered WCUSD #5 student in your household. If you are not interested in participating, you do not need to complete the survey.

https://bit.ly/31r5Ujl

Questions? Please contact the Director of Cafeterias, Ruth Mason: rmm@wcusd5.net or 939-3454

post_text: Summer Reading Opportunity and Free Books! Any student entering 5th-10th grade who would like to participate in a Summer Reading group and have a chance to virtually "visit" with the author, you may pick up a copy of "The Benefits of Being an Octopus" by Ann Braden or "Other Words for Home" by Jasmine Warga on June 19 or June 20 between 10:00 am-noon at the circle drive of Waterloo Jr. High School. There will also be free books ranging from board books through young adult books for students and parents to choose from as well! Check your skyward email for more information!

post_text:
Food delivery updates/reminders for Friday:

- Click the link below for updates to routes E & K
- Bring a bag to carry meals if you are collecting for multiple students.
- Be at the bus stop. To stay as close to time as possible, the driver may not wait long at each stop.
- Be patient on estimated times. We anticipate Friday being closer to schedule now that our drivers know the route, but it could run behind (we will make sure we are not early).
- We have enough meals for anyone that has submitted the interest form up until this afternoon. We will open it back up tomorrow afternoon for Monday's deliveries. If you have submitted the form, we are assuming you will be getting meals daily. There is no need to complete the form multiple times.

It was wonderful seeing all of the smiling faces of students and their families on the routes today! Thank you to all of our wonderful cafeteria workers, teachers, paraprofessionals, administrators, counselors, nurses, custodians, secretaries, and bus drivers for coming together and making this happen.

shorturl.at/gvwMY

post_text:
Waterloo Community Unit School District #5 was recently named the 2019 Best Public School District of Southwest Illinois by the St. Louis Post Dispatch.

PUBLIC SCHOOL DISTRICT
Waterloo Community Unit School District No. 5 is a school district featuring educational programming spanning grades pre-K through 12. The district supports high-quality teaching and learning through meaningful, differentiated curriculum and challenging learning experiences. Visit wcusd5.net or call (618) 939-3453 for more information.

Runners-up: Collinsville School District, Edwardsville School District, Jersey CUSD 100, Triad Community Unit School District #5

https://www.stltoday.com/suburban-journals/illinois/best-of-southwest-illinois-community/collection_7b318c3d-f4b5-5e81-a37d-9b44d644311c.html#15

post_text: The post prom committee is looking for volunteers!
shared_text:
Jennifer O'Brien Kretchmer‎WHS Post Prom
December 10, 2018 at 7:46 PM ·

Parents,

It’s that time of the year again! We have been busy working on details for this year’s upcoming Post Prom event. This is an all night event that is organized to keep WHS students and the community of Waterloo safe on prom night. The evening is filled with inflatables, games, prizes, food, and more! We would love for you to participate in helping us organize fundraising events, as well as the evening itself. We will be having a meeting on Tuesday, January 8 at 6 p.m. in the WHS Library for an informational meeting. If you cannot make it to the meeting but are interested in participating, please e-mail jkretchmer@wcusd5.net, kgoeddel@wcusd5.net, or ayearian@wcusd5.net.

Thank you so much for your support!

Kristen Goeddel,
Jen Kretchmer
Amy Yearian
Post Prom Directors

Please join the WHS Legacy Society in honoring five individuals who have made a positive impact on the world and our community. The Open House will begin at 6:30 pm outside the WHS Auditorium this Thursday, September 14th. At 6:00 pm the Legacy Society will be hosting a short tour of the high school for those who wish to participate. They will have a short program, refreshments and an opportunity to congratulate those members we are honoring.

The 2017 WHS Legacy members are as follows:

Mr. Stephen Schaller, WHS Class of 1985
Margaret L. Marshall CDR USN (Ret.), WHS Class of 1985
Mr. Milton Probasco, WHS Faculty 1952 - 1983
Dr. Walter (Wally) Hoffmann, WHS Class of 1961
Mr. James Brandon, WHS Faculty 1963 - 1987

Please join the WHS Legacy Society in honoring these individuals for their legacies.
